<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; CHRISTMAS MELODIES FROM COMO, COLE AND PAVAROTTI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 'Tis the season for Christmas music programs, and KCET-TV Channel 28 serves up 
three of them Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 At 6 p.m., "Perry Como's Irish Christmas" features the 82-year-old singer on 
standards such as "Little Drummer Boy" and "Silent Night." At 8 p.m. comes "A 
Christmas Special With Luciano Pavarotti," followed at 9 p.m. by "Natalie 
Cole's Untraditional Traditional Christmas." 
</P>
<P>
 On a more serious note, John Walsh is the host of "Smart Kids," a special 
designed to give children information about dealing with dangerous situations, 
at 9 tonight on Fox (Channels 11 and 6). 
</P>
