<HEADLINE>
<P>
GO FOR DUNCE CAPS, FORGET SALARY CAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The resignation of baseball's chief negotiator, Richard Ravitch, marks the 
situation's only progress in months.What the system now needs is to get rid of 
player representative Donald Fehr. 
</P>
<P>
 STAN KAPLAN, Garden Grove 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The problem with baseball is there are not enough general managers who know 
the sport. Day in and day out you hear about some club offering a washed-up or 
overrated player a sizable contract on a chance. 
</P>
<P>
 I'm not talking about Darryl Strawberry; I'm talking about Mitch Williams. 
What were the Astros thinking when they traded him for Doug Jones? Now he's 
with the Angels. 
</P>
<P>
 Owners don't need to implement a salary cap. They need to start using their 
money wisely. 
</P>
<P>
 DON E. EAZELL, Corona 
</P>
