<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: REDONDO BEACH; BRITON 
WITH ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE REPORTED MISSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 68-year-old Englishman with Alzheimer's disease was reported missing Friday, 
two days after he wandered from his daughter's home while walking the family 
dog.  
</P>
<P>
 Edward Henry, who was visiting from London, left the 3500 block of Rindge Lane 
about 2 p.m. Wednesday to walk to a supermarket, police said.They said Henry, 
who speaks with a Cockney accent, was seen walking north on Aviation Boulevard 
at Robinson Lane about 90 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
 He is 5 feet, 9 inches tall, weighs 250 pounds, and has brown eyes and a 
medium complexion. He is missing his front teeth. He was was wearing a 
mustard-colored jacket, mustard-colored pants and brown shoes.  
</P>
<P>
 Henry was walking a white poodle that was wearing a red collar with a brass 
tag. 
