<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; BID TO ALLOW OUTDOOR VENDORS ADVANCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura shoppers may soon be able to buy cappuccino, flowers and hot dogs on 
street corners, thanks to a proposed ordinance approved by a City Council 
committee. 
</P>
<P>
 The council's Economic Committee has recommended that the proposal allowing 
outdoor vendors be forwarded to the city Planning Commission.The commission 
will pass its recommendation on to the City Council for a final vote. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance would allow a vendor who purchases a $50 permit at City Hall to 
sell nonalcoholic beverages, food or produce outdoors in a commercial, 
industrial or park area. 
</P>
<P>
 The issue arose when a coffee vendor wanted to open a stall outside the 
Buenaventura Mall, but found that the city code had no provisions for outdoor 
carts, Councilwoman Rosa Lee Measures said. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
