<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: CANOGA PARK; APPLICATIONS FOR SCHOLARSHIP AVAILABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The First United Methodist Church of Canoga Park is accepting applications for 
a $1,500 scholarship awarded yearly to at least one college junior or senior. 
</P>
<P>
 The scholarship fund was created by the church in memory of Laura Longman, who 
died in 1984 of a heart attack while a student at San Francisco State 
University. 
</P>
<P>
 Longman was ill with heart disease throughout her academic career and had to 
have an experimental heart transplant. 
</P>
<P>
 All college students who will be juniors or seniors in the fall of 1995 and 
who have at least a 2.25 grade-point average qualify for the scholarship. 
Applications are due Feb. 16. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the church at (818) 340-2950. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
