<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; $1 MILLION 
AWARDED HEIRS OF TWO OF THE THREE STOOGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jurors in a financial dispute between the heirs of the Three Stooges awarded 
$1 million in punitive damages Friday to the relatives of Joe (Curly Joe) 
DeRita and Larry Fine. 
</P>
<P>
 The damages were awarded by the Los Angeles Superior Court jury a week after 
relatives of DeRita and Fine won more than $2 million in general damages from 
the heirs of Moe Howard. The plaintiffs sued Howard's grandson, Jeffrey Scott, 
and daughter, Joan Maurer, in 1993, alleging that the defendants were 
shortchanging them on royalties checks from Three Stooges merchandise. The 
verdicts followed three months of testimony and more than two weeks of jury 
deliberations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
