<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; TWO CITIES OFFERING FLU SHOT CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 South County residents can get flu shots at two locations this month. 
</P>
<P>
 The public can take advantage of a flu shot clinic sponsored by the Visiting 
Nurses Assn. this weekend at Sav-On Drugs, 23042 Alicia Parkway, Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 The $10 shots will be administered to those 13 and older from 9:30 a.m. to 
3:30 p.m. Saturday and Sunday. Minors will need parental consent. The program 
accepts Medicare for senior citizens. For information, call (800) 616-SHOT. 
</P>
<P>
 Free flu shots are available every Thursday to seniors and people with 
respiratory illnesses at the Orange County Health Care Agency clinic, 27512 
Calle Arroyo, San Juan Capistrano. 
</P>
<P>
 Nurses will give the shots between 10:30 a.m. and 7:30 p.m. only to seniors 
and people with respiratory problems. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call (714) 248-2200.FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
