<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; DWP WARNS 
OF CON ARTISTS POSING AS UTILITY WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Con artists have been posing as utility workers to burglarize homes, the Los 
Angeles Department of Water and Power warned Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The impostors, who have been working in pairs and targeting mostly elderly 
residents, identify themselves as employees of the DWP or another utility, said 
James Derry, the DWP's customer service director.  
</P>
<P>
 They find a reason to draw the person outside to the meter while one of them 
remains inside to steal money or property, Derry said. DWP field employees 
carry photo identification cards and are generally in uniform. 
</P>
</TEXT>
