<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: 4 POST OFFICES PLAN EXTRA HOURS SUNDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four post offices in Ventura County will open Sunday and Dec. 18 to help 
shorten lines during the U. S. Postal Service's busiest time of the year, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The four offices open from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. on Sundays are: the East Ventura 
Station, 41 S. Wake Forest Ave.; Oxnard main office, 1961 N. C St.; Simi Valley 
main office, 2551 N. Galena Ave., and the Thousand Oaks main office, 3435 
Thousand Oaks Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Those offices are open Monday through Friday from 8:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m., 
except the Oxnard office, which remains open until 6 p.m. All four offices are 
open 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. on Saturdays. PAUL ELIAS 
</P>
</TEXT>
