<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: SUNDAY POSTAL HOURS TO EASE HOLIDAY RUSH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. Postal Service is offering an early Christmas gift to people worried 
about mailing out their Christmas cards in time -- Sunday hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Nine post offices will be open in the San Fernando, Antelope and Santa Clarita 
valleys this Sunday and Dec. 18.Hours on those days will be 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sunday holiday hours will be in effect at the following post offices: 
</P>
<P>
 In the San Fernando Valley, Canoga Park main office, 8201 Canoga Ave.; 
Northridge main office, 9534 Reseda Blvd.; Sherman Oaks Station, 14900 Magnolia 
Blvd.; Studio City Station, 3950 Laurel Canyon Blvd.; the Van Nuys main office, 
15701 Sherman Way, and the Woodland Hills main office, 22121 Clarendon St. 
</P>
<P>
 Both the Burbank main office, 2140 N. Hollywood Way, and the Glendale main 
office, 313 E. Broadway, also will be open. 
</P>
<P>
 In Santa Clarita, the main office will be open at 24355 Creekside Road, as 
will The Postal Store, 23640 Lyons Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancaster main office, located at 1008 W. Avenue J-2, also will 
participate. 
</P>
<P>
 These post offices are also open from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. on Saturdays 
throughout the year. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
