<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CYPRESS; APPLICANTS ACCEPTED FOR COLLEGE CHILD CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress College is accepting spring semester registration for a child care 
program at the Campus Children's Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is designed for children ages 2 through 6. Classes begin Jan. 23. 
The center primarily cares for children of college students, but spaces also 
are available for children of community residents who don't attend the college. 
</P>
<P>
 The Campus Children's Center program is open from 7 a.m. to 4 p.m each Monday 
through Friday during spring semester.  
</P>
<P>
 Parents wishing to register their children can call the center at (714) 
821-5920 on weekdays. The center will be closed Dec. 22 to Jan. 9.BILL BILLITER 
</P>
