<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGNIN IN PALOS VERDES TO CONVERT, REST TO BE SOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEORGE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In a move that completes its plans for ending the operations of the I. Magnin 
retail chain, Federated Department Stores said Friday it will convert the I. 
Magnin in Palos Verdes to a Bullock's store and sell seven remaining Magnin 
sites. 
</P>
<P>
 The phaseout of the 118-year-old I. Magnin chain was announced Nov. 18 by its 
parent, R. H. Macy & Co.Macy will merge later this month with Federated, which 
will control the disposition of the 12-store Magnin chain. 
</P>
<P>
 The Palos Verdes store will be the fifth Magnin to be converted to Macy or 
Bullock's outlets, which remain part of the Federated group. The others are in 
Palm Desert, Woodland Hills, Palo Alto and Walnut Creek. 
</P>
<P>
 The Magnin sites to be sold are in Beverly Hills, Newport Beach, Pasadena, San 
Diego, Carmel, Phoenix and the original San Francisco headquarters. A catalogue 
warehouse in Oakland will also be sold. 
</P>
<P>
 Federated said it decided to convert the Magnin in the Shops at Palos Verdes 
mall after completing negotiations with a developer. It will reopen as a 
Bullock's by Feb. 25. GEORGE WHITE 
</P>
</TEXT>
