<P>
 Consumer Confidence on the Rise: The closely watched University of Michigan 
consumer sentiment index showed consumer confidence still gaining steam as the 
Christmas holidays approach.The university's preliminary December consumer 
sentiment index jumped to 97.7 from 91.6 in the final November report, market 
sources said. The current conditions component of the index was reported to be 
106.7, against 102.1 in November. The expectations index climbed to 92.0 
compared with 84.8 last month. 
