BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rates Drop on 30-Year Mortgages: Thirty-year, fixed-rate mortgages averaged 
9.15% this week, down from 9.23% last week, according to a nationwide survey by 
the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp., released Thursday.The rate was the lowest 
since Nov. 3, when it averaged 9.05%. The average hit a 25-year low of 6.74% in 
October, 1993. On mortgages with rates adjusted yearly, lenders were asking an 
average initial rate of 6.56%, up from 6.47% last week. The rates do not 
include add-on fees known as points. 
