President Hafez Assad for his Lebanese counterpart, Elias Hrawi. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Pelletreau, the assistant U.S. secretary of state for Near East 
affairs, was also in Lebanon to brief Lebanese leaders on Christopher's latest 
talks in Syria and Israel. 
</P>
<P>
 The visit was the first by a senior U.S. envoy to Lebanon in more than a year 
and underlined Washington's interest in advancing Lebanon-Israel negotiations. 
Those talks stalled after negotiations between Israel and Syria, Lebanon's de 
facto power, broke down in February. 
