<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY IN BANKRUPTCY; VOICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Many Orange County residents reacted with frustration and anger at the 
county's financial crisis. Here is a sampling of comments received from readers 
invited to telephone the newspaper's TimesLine number with their comments. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 I think the Orange County credit problem right now is due to the Proposition 
13. Bob Citron was a hero in the county because his investments paid off so 
well that people didn't have to be threatened by this kind of cash short fall. 
Now the chickens have come home to roost and we're going to have to pay the 
price from our taxes now instead of borrowing money, borrowing spending until 
we get ourselves in such a mess. 
</P>
<P>
 HOWARD CARTWRIGHT, 
</P>
<P>
 ANAHEIM  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 This is complete, total fiscal irresponsibility. Who is responsible? I feel 
it's the entire Orange County government supervisors. It was a lack of 
oversight and absolutely irresponsible for the treasurer to leverage the 
financial accounts so that there is a possibility for the financial system 
going the opposite direction of his bet. It was total greed and outrageous. 
Playing the securities market is not for public funds. 
</P>
<P>
 PIERRE HANDL, 
</P>
<P>
 ANAHEIM 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 This is going to have a huge trickle-down effect for everyone in the county, 
and it has a huge effect on financial markets for all municipalities. What led 
to the crisis? Lawyers and politicians lacking enough common sense to have laws 
in place to ensure safe investments are made with the public's money. No public 
money should be able to be used to have a huge margin account. The portfolio 
was invested 3-to-1 on margins and very risky investments. 
</P>
<P>
 VINCE FRENCH, 
</P>
<P>
 IRVINE 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 I feel that this whole crisis is the responsibility of the Board of 
Supervisors and Mr. Ernie Snyder. I feel Mr. Snyder should be removed from his 
office, he was the overseer to Mr. Citron. All the questions that were raised 
during the election, he never followed up on obviously and the same with the 
Board of Supervisors. They backed Mr. Citron the whole way, not once 
questioning any of his actions. 
</P>
<P>
 DENNIS HAMPTON, 
</P>
<P>
 IRVINE 
</P>
