<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIVERSIDE MOTHER HELD AFTER 2-YEAR-OLD IS FOUND SLAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 20-year-old mother was held for questioning Friday after her 2-year-old 
daughter was found slain and her infant son was found in critical condition, 
police reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Sgt. Bob Hanson said details of the incident -- including the manner of 
death -- were being withheld by investigators. Another officer, who asked not 
to be identified, said the children "were covered with blood . . . and we're 
not really sure what happened." 
</P>
<P>
 The department identified the dead child as Tabatha Viramontez and said 
8-month-old Thomas Ryan Mora was in critical condition at Riverside Community 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Carrie Michelle Viramontez was being held for questioning. Police were called 
to the Viramontez home by neighbors after the woman ran from her apartment 
screaming, Hanson said. 
</P>
