PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; ANGELOS-BUCCANEERS TALKS PROGRESSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Baltimore Sun 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Peter Angelos, controlling partner of the Baltimore Orioles, met for more than 
two hours Friday with trustees trying to sell the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and 
reported "substantial progress" in his effort to buy the team and move it to 
Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had some very fruitful discussions and they will continue," Angelos said. 
"We are making substantial progress." 
</P>
<P>
 Angelos has also been negotiating to purchase a minority interest in the Rams 
and move them to Baltimore, but he admitted his city has fallen behind St. 
Louis in the race for the Rams. 
</P>
<P>
 "Certainly, St. Louis is substantially in the lead," Angelos said. "But I 
don't think it's a done deal. That can change overnight." 
</P>
