<HEADLINE>
<P>
SYLMAR GOES FOR ANOTHER TITLE AGAINST CRENSHAW IN CITY 4-A 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAIGE LEECH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sylmar High goes for its second City Section Division 4-A title in the last 
three years today, when it meets Crenshaw at El Camino College. Kickoff is at 
noon. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams last played each other in the quarterfinals in 1992, with Sylmar 
winning, 28-2. 
</P>
<P>
 The top-seeded Spartans (13-0) held on for a 28-27 overtime victory over 
Wilmington Banning in the quarterfinals on their way to the championship game. 
Crenshaw's closest call was a 26-19 victory over league rival Dorsey in last 
week's semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw (12-1) likes to run, with 1,000-yard rushers Farrel Payton and 
Brandon Seals leading the attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar mixes it up. Junior Durell Price, who also starts at linebacker, has 
rushed for 1,770 yards and 26 touchdowns. Quarterback Greg Marquez has passed 
for 1,429 yards and 19 touchdowns. PAIGE LEECH 
</P>
