<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL / ROUNDUP; ALTA LOMA CONTAINS CHAFFEY IN 24-0 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILL ETHERIDGE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Cucamonga Alta Loma limited Ontario Chaffey to 126 yards total offense 
to claim the Southern Section Division VI championship with a 24-0 victory 
Friday night at Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
 Before a packed crowd of 4,500, Alta Loma Coach Tim Nelson was carried off the 
field by his team after the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "Credit the defense with a superb effort," said Nelson, whose team finished 
10-4 after an 0-4 start. "It feels great winning Alta Loma's first ever CIF 
championship." 
</P>
<P>
 Alta Loma opened the scoring in the second quarter when running back Keith 
Starks broke loose on a 49-yard run. Two possessions later, quarterback Aaron 
Gallegos connected with Craig Brooks on a 26-touchdown pass to increase the 
lead to 14-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Starks led the game with 117 yards in 11 carries. Gallegos completed five of 
11 passes for 77 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Chaffey running back Mike Rodriguez was held to 55 yards in 13 carries and 
Eddie Badibanga was held to 41 yards in 16 carries. The Taggers' deepest 
penetration was to the Alta Loma 15-yard line early in the first quarter. WILL 
ETHERIDGE 
</P>
</TEXT>
