<HEADLINE>
<P>
CARDMANIA HEADS ELITE FIELD IN UNDERWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A field of 10 headed by Cardmania is entered in today's $100,000-added Vernon 
O. Underwood Breeders' Cup Stakes at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Cardmania, who has won 16 races and more than $1.4 million in a 69-race career 
that began in 1988, will be ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye and is assigned 120 
pounds for the 14th running of the six-furlong race for 3-year-olds and up. 
</P>
<P>
 An 8-year-old Kentucky-bred gelding, Cardmania has recovered from a serious 
leg injury that almost forced him into retirement last February. 
</P>
<P>
 Others entered in today's race are Lost Pan, who will be ridden by Patrick 
Valenzuela and is assigned 122 pounds; Demaloot Demashoot, Chris Antley, 120; 
Gundaghia, David Flores, 120; Concept Win, Gary Stevens, 120; Saratoga Gambler, 
Martin Pedroza, 120; Wekiva Springs, Kent Desormeaux, 118; Minjinsky, Chris 
McCarron, 116; Polar Route, Corey Black, 116, and Gotta Groove, Laffit Pincay, 
116. 
</P>
