<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL / THOUSAND OAKS TOURNAMENT; WASHINGTON CHOPS DOWN 
WESTLAKE FOR TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Westlake High's disciplined half-court approach was no match for Washington's 
up-tempo attack and the Warriors fell, 78-56, Friday night in the championship 
game of the Thousand Oaks tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Patrick Blake scored a game-high 29 points for the Generals (5-1), 
including 23 in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Washington employed a full-court press and a quick transition game to take a 
12-3 lead. Westlake (2-1) regrouped and took a 38-35 halftime lead, but was 
outscored, 19-6, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Smiley and Billy Miller each scored 12 for Westlake. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 62, Thousand Oaks 59 -- Oak Park took fifth place after blowing 
nearly all of a 19-point lead, but lost guard Brandon Creason for at least a 
month when he collided with a teammate and broke his arm. Shawn Williams led 
the Eagles (2-4) with 21 points. 
</P>
