<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALBOA, KIROVSKI PACE U.S. SOCCER VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A veteran and a rookie teamed up to pace the U.S. National Soccer team to a 
2-0 victory Friday night over the Trinidad & Tobago Under-23 Team. 
</P>
<P>
 Marcelo Balboa, who was named the game's most valuable player, scored in the 
28th minute on a right-footed blast from 20 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Jovan Kirovski, who scored on a second-half penalty kick, set up Balboa by 
chesting down a pass. 
</P>
<P>
 Balboa, who has played more international matches than any other player in 
U.S. soccer history, will earn his 99th career cap Sunday against the Honduras 
national team. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirovski, an 18-year-old Escondido native, joined the national team in 
September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
