<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; MORALES' GOAL GIVES ESPERANZA OVERTIME SOCCER VICTORY OVER GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irene Morales' header in the third minute of sudden death gave Esperanza a 4-3 
victory over Van Nuys Grant in pool play of the Vanguard Cup girls' soccer 
tournament Friday at El Modena High. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza's Tammy Lyon scored the tying goal with 10 seconds left in 
regulation. Jamie Bumstead scored two goals for Esperanza. 
</P>
<P>
 In other pool-play games of the Vanguard Cup girls' tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Belmont Notre Dame, 3, Sunny Hills 1 -- Demerese Salter scored a first-half 
goal for Sunny Hills (1-3). Notre Dame is 4-1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 2, El Toro 1 -- Erin Conners and Liz Delgado scored for 
Capistrano Valley (3-2). Jenny Davis scored for El Toro (2-1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 El Modena 2, San Pedro 0 -- Kaylee Whitfield scored two goals and goalie Marie 
Dillon had four saves for El Modena (4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the first round of the Magnolia girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 7, Buena Park 0 -- Heather Gibson scored four goals for Sonora (1-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Magnolia 4, Santiago 0 -- Shannon Myers, Janet Nghiem, Sofia Diaz and Becky 
Young each scored to lead host Magnolia (2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Aliso Niguel 4, Savanna 0 -- Lauren Franson scored two goals for Aliso Niguel 
(4-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In boys' nonleague soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 2, Kennedy 2 -- Danny Arreguin scored with about five minutes left to 
tie the score for host Kennedy (1-0-2). Luis Sanchez scored two first-half 
goals for Savanna (2-0-1). Nick Poan scored Kennedy's other goal. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 6, Ocean View 0 -- Adam Novak scored three goals and Scott 
Hainlen had five saves and a shutout for the Barons (5-0), who have not allowed 
a goal this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Christian 5, St. Margaret's 2 -- Matt Davenport scored three 
goals to lead visiting Capistrano Valley Christian (1-3). Patrick Moss and Ryan 
Downey each scored one goal and Jeremy Blumberg recorded 13 saves for St. 
Margaret's (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 5, Marina 0 -- Brian Peisner had two goals to lead Santa 
Margarita (6-0-1). Craig Steinmetz made 12 saves for visiting Marina (1-1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 2, Sonora 1 -- Kris Fisher's goal 12 minutes into the second half 
gave Villa Park (1-2-1) the victory. Brett Polakoff gave Villa Park the lead 
with a first-half goal, but Sonora's Aaron Jenkins tied the score, 1-1, with a 
goal early in the second half. Sonora is 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Westminster 4, Anaheim 2 -- Wayne Huelskamp scored twice and John Levenshus 
broke a 2-2 tie with a second-half goal for host Westminster (2-1-1). 
</P>
