<HEADLINE>
<P>
SKIERESZ, HERNANDEZ VOTED BEST VENTURA COUNTY RUNNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Eleazar Hernandez of Camarillo High and Amy Skieresz of Agoura have been 
selected Ventura County boys' and girls' cross-country runners of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez, Southern Section Division I champion, finished second behind Keith 
O'Doherty of Thousand Oaks in the county championships, but he posted a 7-1 
record against O'Doherty. 
</P>
<P>
 Skieresz, State Division II champion, won the award for the third consecutive 
time. She won her third consecutive county, Marmonte League and Southern 
Section titles this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Farrell of Thousand Oaks and Ken Reeves of Nordhoff were named boys' 
co-coaches of the year while Farrell, Reeves and Steve Blum of Buena shared the 
girls' award. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks' boys won their second consecutive State Division I title and 
Nordhoff's boys repeated as Division III champions. Thousand Oaks' girls were 
runners-up in State Division I championships and Nordhoff was fourth in the 
Division III final. Buena won its 12th consecutive Channel League title. JOHN 
ORTEGA 
</P>
