<P>
CARPET; HOW TO KEEP YOUR BEST UNDERFOOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Buying a carpet is a long-term investment, yet many consumers overlook useful 
care and cleaning procedures that can extend the life and appearance of a 
carpet. 
</P>
<P>
 Here are some tips: 
</P>
<P>
 * Shade carpets from direct sunlight and protect them by using mats in 
high-traffic areas.Avoid wearing street shoes indoors -- they bring in dirt; 
avoid walking barefoot, as skin oils can soil carpets. 
</P>
<P>
 * Invest in a quality under-carpet cushion, preferably one made of prime 
polyurethane foam. * Clean up all food or beverage spills promptly. 
</P>
<P>
 * Have carpet restretched if it wrinkles or puckers. Vacuum frequently with an 
upright cleaner and have the carpet professionally cleaned regularly. 
</P>
<P>
 * Move furniture frequently and put pads under legs. If dents occur, steam 
fibers with a steam iron held above the carpet. 
</P>
